    "body": "Hi\r\n\r\nI added this to `~/.spack/packages.yaml` after installing three versions of R.\r\n\r\n```\r\npackages:\r\n  r:\r\n    compiler: [gcc@6.3.0]\r\n    version: [3.4.0]\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen doing `spack load r` or `spack load -r r` older versions of R are shown in `module list`.\r\n\r\n```\r\nuser@server[~]$ module list\r\nCurrently Loaded Modulefiles:\r\n  1) r-3.3.2-gcc-6.3.0-kg66bw6   2) r-3.3.3-gcc-6.3.0-jup76eq   3) r-3.4.0-gcc-6.3.0-ljduq4h\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter reading about [Concretization Preferences](https://spack.readthedocs.io/en/latest/build_settings.html#concretization-preferences) it's unclear to me if what I am trying to do can be accomplished **after** packages are already installed.  Do you know of a way?\r\n\r\nThanks!\r\nDoug",
